<SP>
<SPEAKER>Phile.</SPEAKER>
<P>Yea verely, so thei beare their crosse willingly, paci|ently, and thankfully. For by the crosse are christen men knowe~, as noble mens seruauntes by theyr Lordes cognisances. He that bea|reth not the crosse, is not Christes: For suche as will be his disciples, he co~maundeth them not to seeke how to flee y^e crosse, that they may liue al in pleasure, but he biddeth them take the Crosse vpon their shoulders,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Math. xvi.</NOTE> and folow him. If any man will folow me, (saith our sa|uiour Christ,) let him forsake him <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">elf, and take vp his crosse, and fo|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ow me. The head bare the crosse,
