flames of hell fire: where he was miserablie tormented: contrary|wyse, pore and sick Lazarus, who~ the wicked worlde estemed moste vile, moste abhominable, yea, and vtterly despised and cast away of God,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Esay. lxiiii.</NOTE> whome also fortune neuer fauoured, but aduersitie co~tinual|lie assailed, immediatly after his departure was moste tenderly &amp; ioyfully borne of the blessed Aun|gels of God into the bosome of A|braham,<NOTE PLACE="marg">i. Cor. ii.</NOTE> wher he hath such ioyes as eie hath not sene, nor eare hath heard, nether is any mans hart a|ble to thinke them.</P>
