<P>For he knoweth whereof we bee made, he remembreth that we are but duste. My thoughtes
<PB N="72" REF="49">
(saith God) are to geue you peace and not trouble.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ier. xxix. Why God punisheth vs</NOTE> Though the lord punisheth vs for our sinnes, yet doth he not punishe vs, to cast vs away and to condemne vs, but to call vs vnto repentance, to morti|fie our fleshly lustes, &amp; afterward to make vs the more circumspect in obseruing the rules of our pro|fession, y^t is, the christen profession as that princelike Prophet saith:<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. cxix.</NOTE> It is greatly for my wealth, that thou hast punished me &amp; brought me low, euen that I may learne thy righteous ordinances.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Esay. xxviii.</NOTE> Uexa|tio~ or trouble (saith the Prophet) geueth vnderstanding. And wha~+soeuer we repent &amp; cease to sinne, the Lord straightwais remoueth and taketh away the crosse that he hath laid vpon our backes, and poureth his blessing againe plen|tiously vpon vs. For though he maketh a wou~d,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Iob. v.</NOTE> he geueth a pla|ster,
<PB N="73" REF="49">
though he smite, he maketh whole again.<NOTE PLACE="marg">i. Reg. iii&punc;</NOTE> The Lord killeth &amp; maketh a liue, bringeth down to the graue, and fetcheth vp again. The lord maketh poore, &amp; maketh <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ich, bringeth lowe and lifteth vp again.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Tob. iii.</NOTE> After a storm (O lord) saith holy Toby, thou makest the wea|ther faire &amp; calme: after wepyng and heauines, thou geuest great <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">oy. Thy name (O God of Israel) <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e praised for euer.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Euseb.</SPEAKER>
<P>If God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">oueth a man and entendeth to make him partaker of euerlasting glory: he wil not cease to punishe him, vntill he knowledgeth his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ault, repenteth, &amp; become a newe <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">an.</P>
