<P>Than did you vse your goodes aright. And you were not ritch in the world, but in the Lorde, &amp; of the no~bre of those, of whom it is written: blessed are the poore in spirit,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Math. v.</NOTE> for vnto the~ be|longeth the kingdome of heauen The Psalmograph saith:<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psa. lxii.</NOTE> If rit|ches do abound, set not thy heart vpon them.<NOTE PLACE="marg">i. Cor. vii.</NOTE> And the holy Apostl<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> commaundeth, that they which vse the world should be as thoug<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> they vsed it not. For the fashio<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">
