<SP>
<SPEAKER>Epa.</SPEAKER>
<P>The Lorde my God be thanked, I owe no ma~ any thing, but loue &amp; good wyll. My chief study hath euer bene, to kepe my self out of debt. And if at any tyme I ought any thing, to labour vnto the vtter moste of my power, to dispatche my self of that debt withall expedition. I neue<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> counted other mens goodes min<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> own. That I truly got with min<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> own labour, y^t did I alway coun<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> mine owne, my debtes being onc<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> paid. I owe nothyng, many ow<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> me, but forasmuch as they be por<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> men, &amp; can not pay that they ow<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">
