<SP>
<SPEAKER>Ep.</SPEAKER>
<P>No kind of superstitious custome do I al|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ow. That is godly, I only com|mend. As touching your solempn <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">inging,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Singing.</NOTE> it is all one to me, whi|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">her you sing or say. Those Psal|mes, hymnes, prayses &amp; thankes|geuinges that be appointed to be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ong or said at the burial of y^e faith+<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ul, let them be done in the name <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f God w^tal cherefulnes of mind. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">s for your deuout ringinge,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ringing.</NOTE> I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">raue no more but one <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">el to be e|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">her tolled or rong, for to gather <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">he people together, to heare the
