<SP>
<SPEAKER>Phil.</SPEAKER>
<P>It is not w^t|out cause, that the holy scripture doth so diligently call vs vnto re|pentaunce, faith, and good works in this present worlde. For euer|lasting life euen in this worlde is ether gotten or loste. As God fin|deth vs, so iudgeth he vs. Euerye tree is knowen and iudged by her owne fruite, and not by the fruite of other trees. Euery man lyke|wyse is iudged by his owne wor|kes, &amp; not by the workes of other, as Christ saith to the vnprofitable seruaunt:<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke. xix.</NOTE> Of thine owne mouthe wil I iudge thee, thou euil serua~t. Teophilact saith.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mat. xxv.</NOTE> The vertue of my neighbour shall scacely be i|nough to defend him selfe, so farre is it of,<NOTE PLACE="marg">&rindx;</NOTE> that it can profit me also. For all men shall be declared to be righteous by their owne workes, and not by the workes of theyr
