<P>I beleue &amp; am throwly perswaded, y^t by y^t merits of his precious bloud, which said vnto y^e penitent thefe,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luk. xxiii.</NOTE> this day shalt thou be with me in paradise, my soule immediatly af|ter the departure fro~ this vile bo|dy, shall be receiued vnto glory, &amp; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">se y^e glorious maiestie of God,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xxvii.</NOTE> face to face, as y^e Psalmograph sayth, I beleue to see the pleasures and good thinges of the Lorde in the
