</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Epa.</SPEAKER>
<P>O my co~|science is greuously vexed, trou|bled, &amp; disquieted, while I behold the fearce wrath of God againste sinne, and consider how wicked a life I haue led, &amp; how oft I haue broken Gods holy commaunde|me~ts.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Phi.</SPEAKER>
<P>Fear not dear brother, for though you be neuer so sinfull: God is mercifull. Though youre synnes be great: yet are the mer|cies of God muche greater. God
