might not sin against thee.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Iohn. xv.</NOTE> Now are ye cleane sayde Christe, for th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> word, whiche I spake vnto you. Hereto parteineth the sayinge o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the wyseman.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Sap. xvi.</NOTE> Nether hearbe, no emplasture hath healed them, O lord, but thy worde which healet<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> all thinges. Like vnto this is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> sentence in a certaine Psalme,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. cvii.</NOTE> h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> sent his word, and deliuered the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> from destructio~.</P>
