<P>How long wilt thou forget me (O Lord) for euer?<NOTE PLACE="marg">A praier.</NOTE> How long wilt thou hide thy face from me?<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psalm. xiii.</NOTE> O how long shal I seke coun|cell in my soule, and be so vexed in my heart? How long shall mine e|nemy triumph ouer me? Consider &amp; here me (O Lord, my God) ligh|ten mine eies that I sleepe not in death, least myne ennemy saye, I haue preuailed against him. If I be cast downe, they that trouble me will reioyse at it. But my trust is in thy mercy, &amp; my hart is ioy|ful in thy saluation. I againe for this thy louynge kyndnesse, wyll prayse thy holy name.</P>
