</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Ep.</SPEAKER>
<P>Unto the wil I cry, O Lord my stre~gth,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xxviii</NOTE> thinck no scorn of me, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">east if thou make thee,<NOTE PLACE="marg">A prayer.</NOTE> as though thou heardest not, I become like them, that go downe into the pit. Here the voyce of my humble pe|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">icions when I cry vnto the, whe~
