I cry vnto the, whe~ I hold vp my handes toward the mercy seat of thy holy temple.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xxvii</NOTE> O hyde not thou thy face from me, nor cast thy ser|uaunt awaye in thy displeasure. The sorowes of death haue com|passed me round about,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xviii.</NOTE> and the o|uerflowings of vngodlines made me afraid, The pains of hel came about me, y^t snares of death haue ouertaken me. Be not thou farre from me&punc;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xxii</NOTE> O Lord, thou art my suc+cour, hast thee to helpe me. Dely|uer my soul from the swearde, my dearling fro~ the power of y^e dog. Saue me from the Lions mouth. So shal I declare thy name vnto my brethren, and in the middest of the co~gregation wil I praise thee<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></P>
