worke suche ioyes in your heart, through his holy spirit, as hereto|fore you felt neuer the lyke. And this your ioy, shall neuer be taken from you. Therefore whatsoeuer sathan that old canckred ennemy of mankinde goeth about to per|swade you,<NOTE PLACE="marg">i. Pet. v.</NOTE> beleue hym not, but resiste him with strong faith, euer remembring that he is both a lier and a murtherer. You are a mem|ber of that congregation,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Iohn. viii.</NOTE> whiche is built vpon the rocke Christe,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Math. xvi.</NOTE> a|gainste whome the gates of hell, shall not preuayle. You are a ly|uing stone of the blessed building and spiritual house,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Math. vii.</NOTE> wherof Christ is the head corner stone, though y^e windes blow, the shours of raine descend, and the cruell tempestes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">eate on the house, yet it falleth not, for it is grounded not vpon y^e and,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke. xxii.</NOTE> but vpon the rocke. Sathan <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n this temtation hath desired to
