<P>Beleue this earnest|ly, and it shal not greue you to de|part fro~ your body. For wher as it is now mortal, incorruptible, sick, weake, vile, &amp; lothsome, it shal at y^e generall resurrection, be immor|tal, vncorruptible, whole, strong, precious, and in al poynts lyke to the glorious body of our Lorde, &amp; sauiour Christ Iesus.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Phil. iii.</NOTE> Hear wha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the Apostle saith: our conuersati<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">on is in heauen, from whence we loke for a sauiour, euen the Lorde Iesus Christ, which shal chaung<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> our vile body, that he may mak<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> it like vnto his glorious body, ac|cording to the working, whereby he is able also to subdue al things vnto him selfe.<NOTE PLACE="marg">ii. Cor. v</NOTE> Agayne: We know that if our earthy mansion of this
