<P>It is vnto vs great ioy and comfort, to be with you being so godly mynded. For in you as in a cleare mirrour we beholde our selues, and see what shall become of vs hereafter. Of you as of a liuely scholemaister do we learne, howe we shall behaue our selues, when God layeth the crosse on vs. And we most humbli~ besech God to geue vs the like pa|cience and thankfulnes.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mat. xxvi.</NOTE></P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Epa.</SPEAKER>
<P>The spirite is willing, but the fleshe is
<PB N="514" REF="260">
weake. For in asmuch as I fele in my self present tokens of death, &amp; am not certain how long y^e&punc; Lorde will suffer me to liue, or to enioy y^e vse of speche, I thinke it conue|nient to pray again vnto the lorde my God, and to commend my sin|ful soul into his merciful handes.</P>
